When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this: \(y = \sin(x)\).

\[ y = \sin(x) \]

Remark that sometimes it is necessary to run the algorithms / particular functions of Firebrowse several times to get the data, i.e.if the output of an algorithm or especially a particular function is NULL it doest imply always data absence (the explanation could be a lack of connection to the server) This error appears especially using the services and If the data corresponds to multiple page.Size, e.g.nrow(data)=2*page.Size, then for the next page.Counter () there are no data, so youll get the error Error in data[[page.Counter]] : subscript out of bounds

source("dn_clinical.R")
cohorts = dn_cohorts()
cohort = "BRCA"
brca.clinical = dn_clinical_cohort(cohort)
clinical = dn_clinical(cohorts[1:3])
barcodes = dn_patient_barcodes(clinical) 
tcga_participant_barcode = "TCGA-E9-A2JT" # it is a BRCA patient barcode
page.Size = 25000
gene_ID = dn_gene_ID(tcga_participant_barcode, page.Size)
source("dn_miRNA.R")
tcga_participant_barcode1 = "TCGA-BH-A1EO"  # it is a BRCA patient barcode
miRNA_ID = dn_miRNA_ID (tcga_participant_barcode1) 
cohort = "BRCA"
page.Size = 2000
sort_by =  "tcga_participant_barcode"
mir = miRNA_ID[1]
tcga_participant_barcode2 = ""  # returns all patient barcodes of the cohort "BRCA" in dn_miRSeq
obj = dn_miRSeq(mir, cohort, tcga_participant_barcode2, sort_by, page.Size)
miRNA.brca = dn_miRNA_cohort(miRNA_ID[1:10], cohort, page.Size)
